1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,877
[suspenseful music playing]

2
00:00:08,091 --> 00:00:08,800
[man grunts]

3
00:00:09,634 --> 00:00:10,385
Who are you?!

4
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:12,345
[Marcus] <i>Come with me.</i>

5
00:00:15,890 --> 00:00:16,808
[Marcus] <i>They came for you!</i>

6
00:00:17,308 --> 00:00:18,518
Let's go!

7
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:22,397
- [man grunts]
- [gunshots]

8
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:27,902
[tires screeching]

9
00:00:27,986 --> 00:00:30,530
I was right. I'm now with Datu Rahman!

10
00:00:30,613 --> 00:00:32,073
I need your help.

11
00:00:32,157 --> 00:00:34,993
- [man 1] Coming!
- [woman] Hurry up!

12
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,077
[man 2] Excuse me.

13
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:38,204
[Lara] Why are you just here now?

14
00:00:39,205 --> 00:00:40,623
What could this be for?

15
00:00:41,624 --> 00:00:43,877
[Marcus, in English] <i>It's a high-security</i>
<i>bypass key, sir.</i>

16
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:50,675
[Marcus, in English] <i>Check the area.</i>

17
00:00:50,759 --> 00:00:52,093
[officer] <i>I was right.</i>

18
00:00:52,177 --> 00:00:54,304
<i>Datu was really brought here.</i>

19
00:00:54,387 --> 00:00:55,263
It seems he was only
moved out of here earlier.

20
00:00:57,891 --> 00:00:59,267
[Lara] How could this happen?

21
00:00:59,350 --> 00:01:01,686
Who took you? Who?!

22
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:03,354
[Jalil coughs]

23
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:06,566
Who are you? Are you planning
to take Datu Rahman away?

24
00:01:06,649 --> 00:01:08,526
- Let me out!
- [grunting]

25
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:11,321
This seems to be the man
you are looking for.

26
00:01:11,404 --> 00:01:12,906
And I found out something.
He's the son of Datu Rahman.

27
00:01:12,989 --> 00:01:14,824
[Felix] <i>All right, I'm on my way.</i>

28
00:01:14,908 --> 00:01:17,577
- [groans in pain]
- [gas hissing]

29
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:18,870
- [men screaming]
- [gunshots]

30
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:23,875
You're coming with me.

31
00:01:23,958 --> 00:01:27,003
Who even are you?
Were you the guy I saw earlier?

32
00:01:27,086 --> 00:01:29,255
[Marcus] <i>You also plan</i>
<i>to save Datu Rahman.</i>

33
00:01:31,841 --> 00:01:33,301
[suspenseful music continues]

34
00:01:33,384 --> 00:01:34,844
[Felix screams]

35
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:38,598
[Jalil in muffled voice] You bastards!
Let me out of here!

36
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:47,398
[mysterious theme music playing]

37
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:07,961
[stirring music playing]

38
00:02:11,714 --> 00:02:15,009
[Marcus] <i>Why are they ready</i>
<i>to kill so many people for you?</i>

39
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:20,265
[Marcus] <i>Who are you, Datu Rahman?</i>

40
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:24,394
‪[music concludes]

41
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:27,147
Your uncle's here now.

42
00:02:27,230 --> 00:02:28,106
[Jamilah whimpers]

43
00:02:28,189 --> 00:02:29,232
[Jamilah] Uncle?

44
00:02:29,732 --> 00:02:31,901
Is there any news on Jalil?

45
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:33,403
[somber music playing]

46
00:02:33,486 --> 00:02:34,654
[clicks tongue]

47
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:35,572
Not yet.

48
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:39,617
I've talked to all the people
I know and trust already.

49
00:02:40,493 --> 00:02:42,495
Even Yusuf and Ethan.

50
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:45,081
But they didn't know where Jalil was.

51
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:47,876
What if something bad happened to Jalil?

52
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:48,877
[sobs]

53
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:52,881
- Auntie, what if--
- Jamilah, don't think like that.

54
00:02:53,464 --> 00:02:54,966
Please don't think that.

55
00:02:55,049 --> 00:02:58,303
[morose music playing]

56
00:02:58,386 --> 00:02:59,137
Jamilah…

57
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:01,222
Your brother is strong.

58
00:03:01,306 --> 00:03:05,268
Let's put our faith in Allah,
that he's safe wherever he may be.

59
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:07,645
Omar…

60
00:03:08,146 --> 00:03:10,315
Is there anything else we can do?

61
00:03:10,815 --> 00:03:13,818
We can't reach out to the police yet.

62
00:03:15,278 --> 00:03:16,738
[sobbing] J-Jalil…

63
00:03:16,821 --> 00:03:18,615
[morose music continues]

64
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:19,824
[Norhana mumbles]

65
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:25,163
[sobbing continues]

66
00:03:29,959 --> 00:03:32,003
[tense music playing]

67
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:34,464
- Where is he?
- He's inside.

68
00:03:34,547 --> 00:03:37,467
[suspenseful music playing]

69
00:03:56,152 --> 00:03:58,029
Let's not make this
any longer, Datu Rahman.

70
00:03:58,112 --> 00:04:00,823
[Marcus sighs]

71
00:04:00,907 --> 00:04:02,242
You need to answer my questions.

72
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:08,248
Who abducted you when you
were transferring facilities?

73
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:11,501
What were they planning to do with you?

74
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:16,923
[scoffs]

75
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:19,217
Why didn't they kill you?

76
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:27,600
[Marcus sighs]

77
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:29,269
You want to go home, don't you?

78
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:35,441
Just answer my questions,
and I'll take you home myself.

79
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:36,693
And where would I go home to?

80
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:41,114
You burned our homes down.

81
00:04:41,698 --> 00:04:44,867
You killed my neighbors
like they were animals.

82
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:48,371
You ruined our peaceful lives!

83
00:04:48,454 --> 00:04:50,999
We didn't like what happened.

84
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,085
And we weren't the first ones
to fire our guns.

85
00:04:54,168 --> 00:04:57,755
Tell that to the dead bodies
you left behind on our island!

86
00:04:58,339 --> 00:05:00,925
A lot of people died on your island.
That's true!

87
00:05:02,051 --> 00:05:04,762
But there were also a lot
of casualties in our ranks.

88
00:05:04,846 --> 00:05:06,764
Just to catch you!

89
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:09,267
Why do you matter so much?

90
00:05:09,934 --> 00:05:11,853
Huh? Tell me!

91
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:14,022
Who are you?

92
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:17,775
[tense music playing]

93
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:19,777
[hands slam on table]

94
00:05:21,612 --> 00:05:24,365
[breathing heavily]

95
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:26,075
Guys, have you heard the gossip

96
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:28,286
about the police officers
who've been dying?

97
00:05:28,369 --> 00:05:29,203
It's crazy!

98
00:05:29,787 --> 00:05:32,415
- <i>They've been dying one after another.</i>
- [man] <i>Yes!</i>

99
00:05:32,498 --> 00:05:35,168
[man] You know, all of this started

100
00:05:35,251 --> 00:05:38,546
when Task Force Alpha massacred

101
00:05:38,629 --> 00:05:42,592
innocent people on Damay Island.

102
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:49,057
[woman] Karma is real!

103
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:51,517
I wonder what the police are doing now.

104
00:05:51,601 --> 00:05:52,894
Don't they feel any pity

105
00:05:52,977 --> 00:05:54,645
for the innocent people
getting caught in all this?

106
00:05:58,399 --> 00:06:02,653
They'll probably pin it
on Datu Rahman again.

107
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:04,405
<i>Isn't that always how it goes?</i>

108
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:07,408
<i>Whenever there's trouble,</i>
<i>who do they blame?</i>

109
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:09,410
<i>The ones you don't know!</i>

110
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:11,579
<i>People like us Muslims!</i>

111
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:16,584
Have you seen the theories online?

112
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:19,045
There are so many!

113
00:06:19,128 --> 00:06:22,715
Yeah. Some are saying
a syndicate is behind it.

114
00:06:22,799 --> 00:06:26,177
But others say it's Datu Rahman
getting revenge.

115
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:29,972
[woman] But for me,

116
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:35,770
Agent Marcus Reyes
is really the root of all this.

117
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:37,980
So many people died because of him!

118
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:40,191
[woman] <i>It's insane!</i> [huffs]

119
00:06:40,274 --> 00:06:42,568
<i>What is happening to our country?</i>

120
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:45,613
This isn't even about the truth anymore.

121
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:50,284
Because people believe their own biases

122
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:52,453
instead of finding out what's real!

123
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:54,831
[woman] <i>That's the truth!</i>

124
00:06:55,414 --> 00:06:58,584
[pensive music playing]

125
00:07:00,294 --> 00:07:01,587
[gate rattles]

126
00:07:02,171 --> 00:07:03,673
- [sighs]
- [Usman] Wait.

127
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:05,758
Do you want me to talk to him?
Maybe I can help.

128
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:06,676
[tense music playing]

129
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:08,761
He knows we're working together.

130
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:11,055
He won't fall for it easily.

131
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:14,058
Besides, I've already done everything.

132
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:16,144
He really has no intention
of telling the truth.

133
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:18,688
What if he really doesn't know anything?

134
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:22,733
Impossible.

135
00:07:25,194 --> 00:07:27,363
There's a reason he was abducted.

136
00:07:27,864 --> 00:07:30,032
He's hiding something, I'm sure of it.

137
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:31,576
What's your plan now?

138
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:33,661
How long are you going to keep him here?

139
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:36,497
‪[heavy breathing]

140
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,335
Until I solve all of this.

141
00:07:42,378 --> 00:07:45,339
No one should know
that we have Datu Rahman.

142
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:48,885
He's the key to all this chaos.

143
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:52,555
As long as we have him, we have leverage.

144
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:56,309
But be careful.

145
00:07:56,809 --> 00:07:59,103
We don't know who the real enemies are.

146
00:08:00,062 --> 00:08:04,066
And they won't stop until
they get Datu Rahman back.

147
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:06,277
And remember this.

148
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,739
- They won't hesitate to kill you
- [keys clink]

149
00:08:10,448 --> 00:08:12,241
once they find out what you're doing.

150
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:13,910
I know.

151
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:17,163
That's why we need to be careful.

152
00:08:18,664 --> 00:08:19,749
[Marcus breathes heavily]

153
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:22,001
I need to know the truth…

154
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:25,129
before they kill me.

155
00:08:25,713 --> 00:08:28,424
[suspenseful music playing]

156
00:08:29,383 --> 00:08:30,510
[Jalil breathing heavily]

157
00:08:30,593 --> 00:08:31,761
You bastards!

158
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:33,262
[suspenseful music playing]

159
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:34,180
Let me go!

160
00:08:35,556 --> 00:08:36,974
Let me go!

161
00:08:37,558 --> 00:08:41,604
[Jalil grunting]

162
00:08:41,687 --> 00:08:47,693
[breathes heavily, grunts]

163
00:08:48,694 --> 00:08:50,780
[music intensifies]

164
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:10,883
[chair thuds]

165
00:09:12,885 --> 00:09:13,886
‪[Jalil whimpers]

166
00:09:17,848 --> 00:09:19,684
[grunts] Who are you?!

167
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:21,602
What do you need?!

168
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:29,610
[Jalil sighs, groans]

169
00:09:37,326 --> 00:09:41,581
[tense music continues]

170
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:07,982
‪[music concludes]

171
00:10:11,819 --> 00:10:15,406
[cutlery clinking]

172
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:20,369
[somber music playing]

173
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:22,830
We invited you here,

174
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:27,293
those of us who remained
as members of the TFA,

175
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:30,338
along with the entire NLEA and SID,

176
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:32,715
to check on you.

177
00:10:33,549 --> 00:10:36,510
We want to thank you…

178
00:10:37,011 --> 00:10:38,512
for granting our request.

179
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:40,514
Of course, Sir Marcus.

180
00:10:41,223 --> 00:10:43,059
We really want this to happen,

181
00:10:43,142 --> 00:10:45,519
especially my son Richard, because…

182
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:48,606
he misses his brother so much.

183
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:55,321
[melancholic music playing]

184
00:10:55,404 --> 00:10:59,075
When I graduated summa cum laude
from my degree in civil engineering,

185
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:03,412
I promised Patrick
that he and Mama will be the ones

186
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:07,541
to confer the medal on me. Unfortunately,

187
00:11:08,542 --> 00:11:12,922
that's not going to happen anymore.
He's not coming home.

188
00:11:13,547 --> 00:11:14,673
I feel sorry for my brother.

189
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:16,384
It's unfair.

190
00:11:16,467 --> 00:11:20,596
He set aside all his dreams
just so I could finish my studies.

191
00:11:21,389 --> 00:11:23,724
And now that it's my turn
to make it up for him,

192
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:25,601
he's gone.

193
00:11:26,102 --> 00:11:28,312
I can now focus on my love life.

194
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:30,648
My brother is done
with his degree in civil engineering.

195
00:11:30,731 --> 00:11:32,441
- [man 1] Wow!
- [man 2] Congrats!

196
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:33,359
[overlapping dialogue]

197
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:38,239
We also get sad
whenever we remember Russel.

198
00:11:38,322 --> 00:11:40,449
He's our only child.

199
00:11:41,033 --> 00:11:42,785
Do you know how…

200
00:11:42,868 --> 00:11:46,038
how parents cope
with the loss of their child?

201
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:48,833
[breathes deeply]

202
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:53,504
How do we get used
to celebrating Christmas

203
00:11:54,713 --> 00:11:55,881
and birthdays,

204
00:11:55,965 --> 00:12:02,096
knowing they won't be coming home
to celebrate those with you?

205
00:12:03,222 --> 00:12:04,640
[sniffles]

206
00:12:04,723 --> 00:12:09,019
Actually, before your mission
on the island,

207
00:12:09,103 --> 00:12:14,150
I knew that when he returned,
he would surprise me with a proposal.

208
00:12:15,192 --> 00:12:17,361
[chuckles] I even got pissed at him.

209
00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:21,740
I said I didn't want that.
It was too corny.

210
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:25,161
[sobs]

211
00:12:25,244 --> 00:12:27,955
But if I only knew
that's what's going to happen,

212
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:33,043
he could propose ten times,

213
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:36,422
and I'd say yes over and over.

214
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:42,178
Gemma.

215
00:12:42,261 --> 00:12:43,512
[sighs]

216
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:47,391
Even if you and Russel didn't get married,

217
00:12:47,975 --> 00:12:51,187
we'll still treat you
like our own for life.

218
00:12:55,274 --> 00:12:59,236
I want you to keep
Russel's engagement ring.

219
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:01,697
It's yours anyway.

220
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:08,078
[Gemma crying]

221
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:14,502
When I get home,
I'll be proposing to my girlfriend.

222
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:16,170
- [man 1] Shh.
- We'll finally get married.

223
00:13:16,253 --> 00:13:17,713
- [man 2] Nice.
- [man 3] Wow. Congrats.

224
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:22,676
My dears, did you think Harold
was my only grandchild?

225
00:13:23,385 --> 00:13:26,597
[sniffles] I have a lot. But…

226
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:29,433
why do I feel this way?

227
00:13:30,017 --> 00:13:33,562
Whether you just have one or a lot…

228
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:39,818
when you lose a loved one,
the pain is just the same.

229
00:13:40,402 --> 00:13:42,863
It's as if my world collapsed.

230
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:48,911
He had no parents to look after him.

231
00:13:48,994 --> 00:13:50,329
That's why he grew up with me.

232
00:13:52,706 --> 00:13:55,751
And he was such a sweet child.

233
00:13:55,834 --> 00:13:57,962
You know what? Despite your many missions,

234
00:13:58,504 --> 00:14:01,840
he'd still travel to Quezon to see me.

235
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:04,843
Both Cuchy and him.

236
00:14:08,055 --> 00:14:11,892
[sniffles] Thank you,
because you're keeping him, Sir Felix.

237
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:15,563
He really looks well-cared for.

238
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:16,730
[chuckles softly]

239
00:14:17,606 --> 00:14:20,693
You know what?
He treated him like his own son.

240
00:14:21,527 --> 00:14:22,987
[woman sniffles]

241
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:25,406
Don't worry.

242
00:14:26,782 --> 00:14:29,034
I'm going to take care of Cuchy

243
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:32,872
just like Harold took care of him.

244
00:14:32,955 --> 00:14:34,999
I will give him the same love.

245
00:14:35,499 --> 00:14:38,210
And maybe even more
than the love Harold gave him.

246
00:14:38,294 --> 00:14:41,088
Cuchy is not just a dog.

247
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:43,007
He's more than a family to me.

248
00:14:43,090 --> 00:14:45,259
- [Felix] Fine, fine.
- He's so cute.

249
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:50,264
I'll look after Cuchy.

250
00:14:50,764 --> 00:14:51,765
I promise.

251
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:53,183
[softly] Thanks.

252
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:54,393
[sniffles]

253
00:14:56,937 --> 00:14:58,022
Uh…

254
00:14:58,105 --> 00:15:00,399
It's good that we're all together today.

255
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:02,985
Uh… We can be there for each other.

256
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:09,158
We can share each
of our existential problems.

257
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:12,536
[sniffles, in English] Excuse me.

258
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:15,456
[footsteps retreating]

259
00:15:16,624 --> 00:15:19,543
[melancholic music playing]

260
00:15:33,265 --> 00:15:34,391
[exhales forcefully]

261
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:40,522
[melancholic music continues]

262
00:15:56,830 --> 00:16:03,796
[muffled sobbing]

263
00:16:11,887 --> 00:16:13,180
[crying]

264
00:16:15,307 --> 00:16:16,684
[crying]

265
00:16:18,686 --> 00:16:21,730
Sir Marcus, how's the investigation going?

266
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:24,817
Are there any leads on who
killed Oliver and the others?

267
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:27,486
[footsteps approaching]

268
00:16:27,569 --> 00:16:29,780
Right now, there are a few leads.

269
00:16:29,863 --> 00:16:32,491
[in English] But everything
is still under investigation.

270
00:16:32,574 --> 00:16:35,035
We apologize for the delay.

271
00:16:35,744 --> 00:16:38,622
However, we are doing everything we can

272
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:40,416
to catch who did this…

273
00:16:40,499 --> 00:16:44,294
[somber music playing]

274
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:47,464
…to Russell, Patrick,

275
00:16:48,257 --> 00:16:50,968
Oliver, and Harold.

276
00:16:51,051 --> 00:16:53,887
[somber music continues]

277
00:17:14,074 --> 00:17:19,705
[vlogger] <i>Agent Marcus Reyes</i>
<i>is behind all this!</i>

278
00:17:19,788 --> 00:17:23,375
<i>A lot of people died</i>
<i>because of him. It's insane!</i>

279
00:17:23,459 --> 00:17:26,628
[exhales in frustration]
<i>What's happening to our country?</i>

280
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:29,256
[footsteps approaching]

281
00:17:30,674 --> 00:17:33,510
- [disconnected line beeping]
- [Jamilah crying softly]

282
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:38,015
[Jamilah inhales sharply]

283
00:17:42,436 --> 00:17:43,729
Nurse Jamilah.

284
00:17:44,605 --> 00:17:47,858
[somber music playing]

285
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:49,318
Are you okay?

286
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:52,488
[voice shaking] Um…

287
00:17:55,115 --> 00:17:56,116
I'm fine.

288
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,242
[inhales]

289
00:17:57,826 --> 00:18:01,371
I've noticed since earlier
that you seem sad.

290
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:07,294
It's not that. Um… I'm just a bit tired
from working in the ER.

291
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:09,254
It gets me burned out sometimes.

292
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:11,882
[in English] Alright.

293
00:18:11,965 --> 00:18:14,676
Okay, I'm not going to bother you anymore.

294
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:18,847
But if you need anything, or…

295
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:23,310
if you need someone to talk to,
I'm just here, okay?

296
00:18:26,563 --> 00:18:27,606
Thank you.

297
00:18:29,858 --> 00:18:31,902
- Alright.
- [Jamilah inhales]

298
00:18:31,985 --> 00:18:34,363
[somber music continues]

299
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:38,283
[Jamilah exhales]

300
00:18:39,451 --> 00:18:41,161
You, too, Doctor.

301
00:18:41,745 --> 00:18:43,997
If you also need anything…

302
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:46,959
I'm just right here.

303
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:51,380
Alright.

304
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:06,979
[Jamilah exhales deeply]

305
00:19:07,521 --> 00:19:11,692
We keep losing our comrades day after day!

306
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:13,819
[tense music playing]

307
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:15,529
But until now…

308
00:19:17,239 --> 00:19:19,116
we still don't know

309
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:23,704
who's doing this to us!

310
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:28,333
[in English] Goddamn it!

311
00:19:31,086 --> 00:19:33,297
The media's devouring us alive!

312
00:19:35,340 --> 00:19:37,342
Aren't you ashamed of yourselves?!

313
00:19:37,426 --> 00:19:40,012
[tense music continues]

314
00:19:50,355 --> 00:19:51,523
[in English] Yes, sir!

315
00:19:52,357 --> 00:19:55,235
Just tell me what you want me to do.

316
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:56,737
I'll do it, sir.

317
00:19:56,820 --> 00:19:59,823
[in English] You know I'm a good
and loyal soldier, sir!

318
00:19:59,907 --> 00:20:01,909
[tense music continues]

319
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:11,835
If Datu Rahman's group
did kill our comrades,

320
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:14,671
then this shouldn't happen again!

321
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:16,506
Do you understand?!

322
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:21,511
We need to find Datu Rahman!

323
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:25,557
- Is that clear?!
- [all, in English] Yes, sir!

324
00:20:26,099 --> 00:20:30,687
[clapping slowly]

325
00:20:31,271 --> 00:20:32,814
[Manuel] Good job.

326
00:20:34,650 --> 00:20:40,155
[in English] That speech
was utterly moving.

327
00:20:41,031 --> 00:20:45,494
I'm sure that because of that,

328
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:50,415
we'll finally resolve the crisis

329
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:54,461
that you yourselves created.

330
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:59,174
[Manuel chuckling, clapping]

331
00:21:24,283 --> 00:21:26,743
Tell me, Emil.

332
00:21:27,452 --> 00:21:32,457
How are you running things
here at the SID?

333
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:36,795
When I founded
the Special Investigations Division

334
00:21:36,878 --> 00:21:40,215
and led it for so many years,

335
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:43,135
I never slipped up.

336
00:21:43,218 --> 00:21:45,137
[in English] Not even once!

337
00:21:45,637 --> 00:21:47,180
And take note.

338
00:21:47,764 --> 00:21:52,561
[in English] I was much younger then
than you are now.

339
00:21:52,644 --> 00:21:53,812
[in English] Yes.

340
00:21:54,438 --> 00:21:55,731
[in English] I remember, sir.

341
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:59,359
You were the youngest colonel
during that time.

342
00:21:59,443 --> 00:22:01,320
[in English] Exactly.

343
00:22:01,403 --> 00:22:03,280
Now tell me.

344
00:22:03,363 --> 00:22:05,615
How can you expect
to be promoted as general

345
00:22:05,699 --> 00:22:10,662
if you can't even do one thing right?

346
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:12,289
Hmm?

347
00:22:12,789 --> 00:22:17,919
Did you know that the Muslim Affairs

348
00:22:18,837 --> 00:22:22,341
is now watching you closely?

349
00:22:22,966 --> 00:22:28,388
They're planning to send an officer

350
00:22:28,472 --> 00:22:30,348
to monitor everything.

351
00:22:31,308 --> 00:22:32,976
W-What do you mean--

352
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:37,314
The division I built

353
00:22:37,397 --> 00:22:43,070
is now treated like a child
needing a nanny!

354
00:22:43,153 --> 00:22:45,989
[tense music continues]

355
00:22:46,073 --> 00:22:51,161
Your failures embarrass me personally.

356
00:22:52,537 --> 00:22:53,747
[in English] I'm sorry, sir.

357
00:22:54,998 --> 00:22:56,166
I'll fix it.

358
00:22:56,249 --> 00:23:00,378
[in English] Walk the talk.

359
00:23:15,852 --> 00:23:19,231
[door clicks open and shut]

360
00:23:23,068 --> 00:23:26,238
- [digital whirring]
- [keyboard clacking]

361
00:23:30,325 --> 00:23:32,327
[music intensifies]

362
00:23:32,410 --> 00:23:36,206
[suspenseful music playing]

363
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:37,624
[bubble warp]

364
00:23:40,669 --> 00:23:44,923
IS EVERYTHING READY?

365
00:23:45,006 --> 00:23:49,094
YES, SIR

366
00:23:50,303 --> 00:23:53,056
[music intensifying]

367
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:55,350
[gunshots]

368
00:24:10,073 --> 00:24:14,369
- [device buzzing]
- [ominous music playing]

369
00:24:25,839 --> 00:24:29,050
<i>In light of recent operational lapses</i>
<i>and the growing sensitivity of the current</i>

370
00:24:29,134 --> 00:24:32,512
<i>appointment of a Liaison Officer</i>
<i>to the Special Investigation Division.</i>

371
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:34,764
<i>Effective immediately, the office</i>
<i>is mandated to join and monitor</i>

372
00:24:41,730 --> 00:24:45,275
<i>all investigations and field operations</i>
<i>within the Agency as deemed necessary.</i>

373
00:24:45,358 --> 00:24:48,111
<i>…your full cooperation in providing</i>
<i>unrestricted access to all case files…</i>

374
00:25:02,584 --> 00:25:03,835
- [frustrated shout]
- [glass shatters]

375
00:25:03,919 --> 00:25:09,966
[music intensifying]

376
00:25:15,388 --> 00:25:16,264
[tense music playing]

377
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:19,226
[Marcus] <i>Everyone thinks</i>
<i>that you're a murderer.</i>

378
00:25:19,309 --> 00:25:20,185
<i>That you're a criminal.</i>

379
00:25:20,268 --> 00:25:24,022
Whoever is behind these videos
wants public outrage.

380
00:25:24,105 --> 00:25:25,440
They want to make you the scapegoat.

381
00:25:25,523 --> 00:25:26,274
But why you?

382
00:25:26,358 --> 00:25:28,193
Sir, it could've been released
to change the narrative.

383
00:25:28,276 --> 00:25:30,904
It's either edited or made
by artificial intelligence.

384
00:25:30,987 --> 00:25:32,864
You sure sound confident

385
00:25:32,948 --> 00:25:34,783
that Datu Rahman was not
the guy in the video.

386
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:35,909
[Azuelo] <i>Did you talk to him?</i>

387
00:25:35,992 --> 00:25:38,703
<i>Did you see that he was</i>
<i>not there that night?</i>

388
00:25:38,787 --> 00:25:41,706
I've known Datu Rahman for a long time.
He couldn't have done that.

389
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:44,292
I'm worried about Jamilah and Jalil.

390
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:45,835
[Norhana] <i>Poor kids.</i>

391
00:25:45,919 --> 00:25:48,922
<i>They'll surely be affected</i>
<i>by what's happening to their father.</i>

392
00:25:49,005 --> 00:25:51,216
[Jalil] <i>Father, I'm going to find you.</i>

393
00:25:51,299 --> 00:25:53,760
<i>I'll flush out those bastards</i>
<i>from their den.</i>

394
00:25:53,843 --> 00:25:57,222
<i>The ones who ruined your life</i>
<i>and our neighbors' lives.</i>

395
00:25:57,305 --> 00:25:59,849
Behave, all of you. He's coming.

396
00:26:02,185 --> 00:26:03,520
[Marcus] <i>Was that on purpose?</i>

397
00:26:05,230 --> 00:26:06,398
Police Major Allan Espina.

398
00:26:06,481 --> 00:26:09,943
[Azuelo] <i>He's the special liaison officer</i>
<i>sent by the Muslim Affairs.</i>

399
00:26:10,026 --> 00:26:12,028
<i>He was assigned in Mindanao</i>
<i>for more than a decade.</i>

400
00:26:12,112 --> 00:26:14,990
Agent Marcus Reyes,
I'm excited to work with you.

401
00:26:15,073 --> 00:26:17,158
[Lara] <i>Why can't I access your records?</i>

402
00:26:17,242 --> 00:26:18,994
<i>What's your secret, Espina?</i>

403
00:26:19,077 --> 00:26:20,036
[in English] <i>What are you?</i>

404
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:22,289
<i>Are you a deep-cover agent?</i>

405
00:26:22,372 --> 00:26:23,456
What are you doing here?

406
00:26:23,540 --> 00:26:28,003
I would like to know the cause
of the massacre on the island.

407
00:26:28,086 --> 00:26:30,797
Those are my team's files.
You can't just dig into them.

408
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:32,257
Too bad. I'm already going through them.

409
00:26:32,340 --> 00:26:34,217
[Marcus] <i>I know that you</i>
<i>have been following me.</i>

410
00:26:34,301 --> 00:26:35,427
<i>What do you need from me?</i>

411
00:26:35,510 --> 00:26:36,803
I'm just doing my job.
